  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.56,
      "end": 5.7,
      "text": "This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 5.7,
      "end": 9.38,
      "text": "information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 10.46,
      "end": 15.7,
      "text": "Asop's fable, the Ass and his burdens. A peddler who owned an Ass one day bought a quantity",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 15.7,
      "end": 20.64,
      "text": "of salt and loaded up his beast with as much as he could bear. On the way home, the Ass",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 20.64,
      "end": 24.98,
      "text": "stumbled as he was crossing a stream and fell into the water. The salt got thoroughly",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 24.98,
      "end": 29.32,
      "text": "wetted and much of it melted and drained away so that, when he got on his legs again,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.74,
      "end": 34.06,
      "text": "the Ass found his load had become much less heavy. His master, however, drove him back",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 34.06,
      "end": 38.04,
      "text": "to town and bought more salt, which he added to what remained in the pan years, and started",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 38.04,
      "end": 42.86,
      "text": "out again. No sooner had they reached a stream than the Ass laid down in it and rose, as",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 42.86,
      "end": 47.82,
      "text": "before, with a much lighter load. But his master detected the trick, and turning back",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 47.82,
      "end": 52.54,
      "text": "once more bought a large number of sponges and piled them on the back of the Ass. When",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 52.54,
      "end": 57.12,
      "text": "they came to the stream, the Ass again laid down. But this time, as the sponges soaked",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 57.12,
      "end": 62.2,
      "text": "up large quantities of water, he found, when he got up on his legs, that he had a bigger",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 62.2,
      "end": 66.48,
      "text": "burden to carry than ever. He may play a good card once too often.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 67.92,
      "end": 76.08,
      "text": "End of the Ass and his burdens, read by Patrick McNeil, www.jacpat.com.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
